I'm Roland. I write software and occasionally words.

I build things, mostly tools I wanted myself and couldn't find. Most of what I make starts with a problem I came across myself, and if others find it useful that's a bonus. Lately I've been spending more time in machine learning and data, still figuring out the landscape there.

Outside of code I draw and do some graphic design. It slows me down in a good way. I also write, mostly about whatever I'm currently curious about or working through.
